WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.009 --> 00:00:10.218
[tense music playing]

2
00:00:12.429 --> 00:00:13.471
[both grunt]

3
00:00:14.097 --> 00:00:15.223
[grunting]

4
00:00:16.057 --> 00:00:17.057
Go!

5
00:00:22.814 --> 00:00:23.814
Whoa!

6
00:00:27.944 --> 00:00:28.944
[grunts]

7
00:00:31.823 --> 00:00:32.823
[grunts]

8
00:00:34.617 --> 00:00:35.869
[both panting]

9
00:00:39.414 --> 00:00:40.498
[grunts]

10
00:00:41.624 --> 00:00:42.917
[music intensifies]

11
00:00:44.544 --> 00:00:46.755
- [gasps]
- Stop!

12
00:00:46.838 --> 00:00:48.214
[panting]

13
00:00:51.092 --> 00:00:52.092
Damn it!

14
00:00:52.594 --> 00:00:53.428
Drop the bag!

15
00:00:53.511 --> 00:00:55.513
[whimpering] Oh. shit!

16
00:00:56.765 --> 00:00:58.516
- [goon] Come here!
- [Woo-jin panting]

17
00:00:58.600 --> 00:00:59.601
[grunts]

18
00:00:59.684 --> 00:01:00.852
Start the car!

19
00:01:02.937 --> 00:01:04.647
Hurry up! Hurry. Run faster.

20
00:01:08.443 --> 00:01:10.195
Hurry. hurry! Come on!

21
00:01:11.654 --> 00:01:13.198
Start the car!

22
00:01:15.075 --> 00:01:17.202
- Bastards.
- [Woo-jin] Run faster!

23
00:01:17.285 --> 00:01:18.536
- Hurry!
- [Hyeon-ju grunts]

24
00:01:20.163 --> 00:01:21.498
[Gun-woo] Please hurry up.

25
00:01:21.581 --> 00:01:24.793
Come on. Door. Door. Door.
Come on. let's go!

26
00:01:24.876 --> 00:01:26.127
[tires screeching]

27
00:01:29.589 --> 00:01:31.257
[all panting]

28
00:01:35.637 --> 00:01:37.263
God dammit.

29
00:01:37.347 --> 00:01:39.349
[theme music playing]

30
00:02:00.745 --> 00:02:04.249
BLOODHOUNDS

31
00:02:05.083 --> 00:02:08.837
People borrowing from Kim Myeong-gil
is way more than we thought.

32
00:02:09.337 --> 00:02:12.340
They all enter the bar
in one-hour intervals.

33
00:02:13.174 --> 00:02:15.426
Some of them in official police vehicles.

34
00:02:15.927 --> 00:02:16.803
[inhales sharply]

35
00:02:16.886 --> 00:02:18.388
I don't know his name.

36
00:02:18.972 --> 00:02:21.474
but there was also
a professional baseball player.

37
00:02:21.558 --> 00:02:22.684
[inhales deeply]

38
00:02:23.226 --> 00:02:24.435
[sighs deeply]

39
00:02:24.519 --> 00:02:27.105
Yeah. well. seems he's expanded his reach.

40
00:02:27.605 --> 00:02:28.605
[inhales deeply]

41
00:02:35.238 --> 00:02:37.240
[coughing]

42
00:02:38.741 --> 00:02:39.741
[coughs]

43
00:02:40.660 --> 00:02:41.660
[coughs]

44
00:02:43.454 --> 00:02:44.454
[Mr. Choi coughs]

45
00:02:45.832 --> 00:02:48.960
I knew it
that Myeong-gil was an ex-convict.

46
00:02:50.086 --> 00:02:51.504
He begged for my help.

47
00:02:51.588 --> 00:02:53.756
He said all he wanted was a fresh start.

48
00:02:53.840 --> 00:02:54.840
[inhales sharply]

49
00:02:55.300 --> 00:02:56.759
And like an idiot...

50
00:02:59.137 --> 00:03:00.930
[sighs] I fell for it.

51
00:03:03.183 --> 00:03:05.143
After Myeong-gil screwed me.

52
00:03:06.436 --> 00:03:08.521
I went into hiding with Mr. Oh.

53
00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:12.192
That's when I heard rumors
that he'd started a company

54
00:03:12.859 --> 00:03:15.236
using the money and bonds
he had stolen from me.

55
00:03:17.197 --> 00:03:19.782
I should've taken care of him
a long time ago.

56
00:03:20.867 --> 00:03:22.785
I taught him everything.

57
00:03:22.869 --> 00:03:24.245
[inhales deeply]

58
00:03:25.163 --> 00:03:26.331
[exhales deeply]

59
00:03:27.916 --> 00:03:29.250
I didn't have the courage.

60
00:03:31.127 --> 00:03:33.171
I wish I would've gained some by now.

61
00:03:35.757 --> 00:03:37.677
I shouldn't have stopped you
from going after him

62
00:03:37.717 --> 00:03:39.344
and giving him what he deserved.

63
00:03:40.428 --> 00:03:41.428
I'm sorry.

64
00:03:42.847 --> 00:03:45.558
I was too afraid I'd lose you as well.

65
00:03:52.774 --> 00:03:53.816
You've always...

66
00:03:55.818 --> 00:03:58.321
cared for me and protected me
like I was family.

67
00:04:00.531 --> 00:04:02.158
I'm always... [inhales sharply]

68
00:04:02.909 --> 00:04:06.120
...ready to lay my life on the line for you
anytime you need it. sir.

69
00:04:07.580 --> 00:04:08.580
I know you are.

70
00:04:10.708 --> 00:04:11.708
And I'm sorry.

71
00:04:14.420 --> 00:04:15.797
[cell phone vibrating]

72
00:04:20.843 --> 00:04:21.843
Hello.

73
00:04:23.429 --> 00:04:25.223
Okay. [sighs]

74
00:04:26.724 --> 00:04:27.724
Come on back.

75
00:04:31.729 --> 00:04:35.024
So. uh. it seems the kids just got jumped

76
00:04:35.942 --> 00:04:37.527
while they were moving all the money.

77
00:04:38.194 --> 00:04:40.571
- Are they hurt?
- No. they didn't mention it.

78
00:04:41.072 --> 00:04:42.073
But. uh.

79
00:04:43.658 --> 00:04:45.576
they said they lost the money
from the safe.

80
00:04:45.660 --> 00:04:47.287
Are they hurt or not?

81
00:04:48.121 --> 00:04:49.622
I think they're all right.

82
00:04:50.540 --> 00:04:51.540
[exhales deeply]

83
00:04:52.792 --> 00:04:57.463
They also... tied one of them up
but didn't want to finish him off.

84
00:04:57.547 --> 00:04:58.547
Now what?

85
00:05:00.466 --> 00:05:03.761
When an ER receives a patient
that was injured doing something illegal...

86
00:05:03.845 --> 00:05:04.845
[inhales sharply]

87
00:05:04.887 --> 00:05:07.223
...the doctors are obligated
to call the police.

88
00:05:07.849 --> 00:05:10.685
That's why
I used to have surgeons of my own

89
00:05:10.768 --> 00:05:12.353
ready to operate at all times.

90
00:05:13.813 --> 00:05:16.399
I'm pretty sure Myeong-gil must have
a similar arrangement.

91
00:05:17.317 --> 00:05:19.652
I'll go get Du-yeong.
He's gonna find him fast.

92
00:05:19.736 --> 00:05:22.572
- [dramatic music playing]
- [In-beom heavy. rapid breathing]

93
00:05:23.156 --> 00:05:24.991
- [bones crack]
- [shouts. groans]

94
00:05:31.039 --> 00:05:32.665
[yelling]

95
00:05:33.291 --> 00:05:34.751
[In-beom grunting]

96
00:05:40.673 --> 00:05:41.924
[coughing]

97
00:05:47.263 --> 00:05:48.389
[In-beom coughing]

98
00:05:51.642 --> 00:05:53.561
[suspenseful music playing]

99
00:06:11.662 --> 00:06:12.662
Good job.

100
00:06:14.123 --> 00:06:15.123
Hey.

101
00:06:18.753 --> 00:06:19.837
Good job.

102
00:06:20.546 --> 00:06:21.631
Uh. yeah.

103
00:06:22.715 --> 00:06:26.219
Get some sleep. okay?
Come to the restaurant tomorrow.

104
00:06:27.428 --> 00:06:29.389
[hesitating] What? Uh. what for?

105
00:06:30.348 --> 00:06:31.348
For food.

106
00:06:32.642 --> 00:06:33.642
Oh.

107
00:06:35.436 --> 00:06:36.437
Okay?

108
00:06:37.855 --> 00:06:39.399
I don't usually eat lunch.

109
00:06:39.482 --> 00:06:40.942
- You will.
- Yeah.

110
00:06:42.360 --> 00:06:43.360
Go on.

111
00:06:47.490 --> 00:06:48.490
[Hyeon-ju grunts]

112
00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:52.537
- [Gun-woo exhales]
- Hey.

113
00:06:52.620 --> 00:06:54.372
[Mr. Choi grunting]

114
00:06:57.750 --> 00:06:58.793
You okay?

115
00:07:01.170 --> 00:07:03.840
We lost all the money
in the safe. I'm really sorry.

116
00:07:03.923 --> 00:07:05.800
But you're not hurt anywhere. right?

117
00:07:06.467 --> 00:07:07.467
Oh.

118
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:09.428
No.

119
00:07:10.596 --> 00:07:11.806
That's all that matters.

120
00:07:11.889 --> 00:07:13.141
[gentle piano music playing]

121
00:07:13.224 --> 00:07:17.270
Oh. I... I have more boxes to move.
You should sleep.

122
00:07:22.024 --> 00:07:24.026
Hyeong-ju. are you sure you're not hurt?

123
00:07:28.030 --> 00:07:29.030
Yeah.

124
00:07:41.878 --> 00:07:43.254
[shallow breathing]

125
00:08:00.980 --> 00:08:02.565
[In-beom grunting]

126
00:08:15.244 --> 00:08:17.580
[engine revving]

127
00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:21.042
[dramatic music playing]

128
00:08:23.294 --> 00:08:25.894
It's not that I didn't pay them back.
but this guy just came in...

129
00:08:27.548 --> 00:08:29.592
[Jang-do] In-beom is going to be fine.

130
00:08:30.176 --> 00:08:31.511
but his eardrum is busted.

131
00:08:33.137 --> 00:08:35.723
I got a license plate.
I'll run it through tomorrow.

132
00:08:36.682 --> 00:08:37.975
What do you mean "tomorrow"?

133
00:08:39.101 --> 00:08:41.604
That's when
the officers we pay are on duty.

134
00:08:41.687 --> 00:08:42.687
[chuckles]

135
00:08:44.232 --> 00:08:45.608
Watch your tone with me.

136
00:08:48.069 --> 00:08:49.111
Don't push me.

137
00:08:49.779 --> 00:08:50.905
Ah. shit. [clicks tongue]

138
00:08:53.658 --> 00:08:54.658
[lighter clicks]

139
00:08:56.160 --> 00:08:57.160
[Jang-do sighs]

140
00:08:58.162 --> 00:09:01.457
If it's an unregistered vehicle
or fake plates.

141
00:09:01.541 --> 00:09:04.794
is it possible to track it
with the security cameras?

142
00:09:06.295 --> 00:09:08.798
It's definitely possible.
but it would take us a little while.

143
00:09:09.465 --> 00:09:12.260
License plates can be looked up
on the police Intranet.

144
00:09:12.843 --> 00:09:14.883
But if we're talking about
getting security footage.

145
00:09:14.929 --> 00:09:18.808
that's a different story. We'd have to...
be able to get inside control centers.

146
00:09:18.891 --> 00:09:21.011
and I would need to pay off
the right kinds of people.

147
00:09:21.769 --> 00:09:23.020
Money is not an issue.

148
00:09:23.563 --> 00:09:24.939
Just get it done quickly.

149
00:09:25.773 --> 00:09:26.607
Yes.

150
00:09:26.691 --> 00:09:29.193
I want you to find out
who owns the building.

151
00:09:29.944 --> 00:09:32.655
If it's Choi.
you need to get his home address.

152
00:09:33.531 --> 00:09:34.365
Yeah.

153
00:09:34.448 --> 00:09:35.533
You can go now.

154
00:09:36.200 --> 00:09:37.618
Let me talk to Jang-do.

155
00:09:39.203 --> 00:09:40.203
Sir?

156
00:09:42.373 --> 00:09:43.457
You heard me.

157
00:09:47.336 --> 00:09:48.421
Sure.

158
00:09:54.677 --> 00:09:55.677
[lighter clicks]

159
00:10:01.892 --> 00:10:02.892
[lighter clicks]

160
00:10:09.442 --> 00:10:10.442
Beom.

161
00:10:11.235 --> 00:10:12.737
why do you think they left him there?

162
00:10:14.530 --> 00:10:16.282
Is it because they had run out of time?

163
00:10:16.991 --> 00:10:19.160
Jang-do. Jang-do. huh?

164
00:10:20.077 --> 00:10:22.496
You're thinking far too positively
right now.

165
00:10:23.664 --> 00:10:25.458
Think negatively for a change.

166
00:10:26.125 --> 00:10:27.585
Try to understand.

167
00:10:27.668 --> 00:10:29.188
Those bastards are trying to kill you.

168
00:10:29.253 --> 00:10:32.048
You should allow that idea
to drive your thoughts.

169
00:10:32.131 --> 00:10:33.549
So why'd they leave him there?

170
00:10:36.385 --> 00:10:38.387
- They're planning to track him.
- [scoffs]

171
00:10:40.723 --> 00:10:42.016
Okay then.

172
00:10:42.099 --> 00:10:44.769
We need to get more men
and put them at the hospital.

173
00:10:45.603 --> 00:10:46.603
Yes.

174
00:10:48.356 --> 00:10:49.857
And we need to follow Jun-min.

175
00:10:52.777 --> 00:10:54.028
Why? Did he do something wrong?

176
00:10:54.111 --> 00:10:57.281
Uh. I told you to think negatively
about this.

177
00:10:58.449 --> 00:11:00.785
Mr. Choi may have info on him.

178
00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:03.663
Ah.

179
00:11:04.580 --> 00:11:07.208
[inhales sharply]
Jun-min is just a coward.

180
00:11:07.792 --> 00:11:09.502
He's turned way too easily.

181
00:11:10.169 --> 00:11:11.295
It'll be very obvious.

182
00:11:11.379 --> 00:11:13.923
One look at his face.
and he just gives everything away. huh?

183
00:11:15.257 --> 00:11:16.092
Sir.

184
00:11:16.175 --> 00:11:17.259
[inhales sharply]

185
00:11:17.927 --> 00:11:19.053
All right now.

186
00:11:19.762 --> 00:11:21.597
Beom is just a small fry here.

187
00:11:22.598 --> 00:11:23.891
So Lee Du-yeong is our man.

188
00:11:23.974 --> 00:11:25.226
He's got a bike.

189
00:11:25.309 --> 00:11:27.186
That's who they'll send to tail him.

190
00:11:27.269 --> 00:11:28.104
Yeah.

191
00:11:28.187 --> 00:11:30.648
Block the streets and trap him.

192
00:11:33.234 --> 00:11:34.234
Yes.

193
00:11:35.361 --> 00:11:36.821
[chuckles] Should be fun.

194
00:11:36.904 --> 00:11:38.184
- [clicks tongue]
- [music stops]

195
00:11:44.620 --> 00:11:45.620
[exhales deeply]

196
00:11:48.082 --> 00:11:49.082
[exhales deeply]

197
00:11:50.251 --> 00:11:51.251
[exhales deeply]

198
00:11:53.212 --> 00:11:54.714
[heavy breathing]

199
00:12:02.388 --> 00:12:03.388
Oh!

200
00:12:04.056 --> 00:12:05.099
Did you sleep well. sir?

201
00:12:05.850 --> 00:12:07.059
Did you get any sleep?

202
00:12:07.810 --> 00:12:08.644
Yeah.

203
00:12:08.728 --> 00:12:11.105
You got back so late. You should rest now.

204
00:12:11.188 --> 00:12:12.857
I got plenty of sleep. but thank you.

205
00:12:12.940 --> 00:12:14.024
Ah. Gun-woo.

206
00:12:14.525 --> 00:12:16.277
I've been meaning
to talk to you. actually.

207
00:12:16.360 --> 00:12:17.360
Oh.

208
00:12:20.197 --> 00:12:21.574
[Mr. Choi grunting]

209
00:12:22.324 --> 00:12:27.705
Hyeon-ju. uh... You may have noticed
she always has a bit of an edge to here.

210
00:12:27.788 --> 00:12:28.788
Oh.

211
00:12:29.415 --> 00:12:33.085
I think that's the reason why
she acts a little cold at times. [laughs]

212
00:12:33.919 --> 00:12:35.421
Ah. [inhales sharply]

213
00:12:36.505 --> 00:12:38.632
But she seems
to have softened considerably

214
00:12:38.716 --> 00:12:39.916
since meeting you and Woo-jin.

215
00:12:39.967 --> 00:12:42.470
For that. you have my gratitude.

216
00:12:43.804 --> 00:12:45.556
We really enjoyed working with Hyeon-ju.

217
00:12:45.639 --> 00:12:47.057
Oh. very good.

218
00:12:47.141 --> 00:12:49.143
So. the money I paid you in advance.

219
00:12:50.144 --> 00:12:51.144
it's gone.

220
00:12:52.104 --> 00:12:55.775
Oh. so... where did the money go then?

221
00:12:55.858 --> 00:12:58.068
I meant to say that we're even now.

222
00:12:58.152 --> 00:12:59.612
Oh. why?

223
00:12:59.695 --> 00:13:03.741
Do you have any idea
how much money you managed to recover?

224
00:13:04.408 --> 00:13:05.743
Uh. well...

225
00:13:05.826 --> 00:13:06.826
[inhales sharply]

226
00:13:08.412 --> 00:13:09.663
[chuckles softly]

227
00:13:10.748 --> 00:13:14.668
I'm going to give you a nice bonus
for a safe transport.

228
00:13:14.752 --> 00:13:16.170
Oh. uh... [inhales sharply]

229
00:13:17.087 --> 00:13:19.548
I'd like to pay it back
by putting my fair share of work. sir.

230
00:13:19.632 --> 00:13:21.383
You've already done your share.

231
00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:24.845
You three managed
to retrieve a considerable sum.

232
00:13:26.096 --> 00:13:27.096
[exhales deeply]

233
00:13:27.681 --> 00:13:31.352
So from this moment.
you're not indebted to me anymore.

234
00:13:31.936 --> 00:13:36.440
Get your mom
and go open a new café somewhere nice.

235
00:13:38.150 --> 00:13:40.152
I'll make all the necessary investments.

236
00:13:40.236 --> 00:13:41.487
[chuckles softly]

237
00:13:43.531 --> 00:13:45.866
Thank you so much. Mr. Choi.

238
00:13:46.367 --> 00:13:49.537
I want to help you catch Kim Myeong-gil

239
00:13:50.746 --> 00:13:52.081
I'll do that until the very end.

240
00:13:52.164 --> 00:13:53.707
You've been very helpful.

241
00:13:53.791 --> 00:13:56.418
I know that.
but I'd like to see it to the very end.

242
00:13:57.920 --> 00:13:58.920
Why?

243
00:13:59.880 --> 00:14:00.965
To repay my debt.

244
00:14:01.549 --> 00:14:03.008
You've done enough already.

245
00:14:03.092 --> 00:14:04.718
It's not enough in my book. sir.

246
00:14:05.886 --> 00:14:08.097
It's not over until it's over for real.

247
00:14:09.515 --> 00:14:12.434
[chuckles] Yeah.

248
00:14:14.270 --> 00:14:17.523
- It's not over till it's over for real.
- [exhales deeply]

249
00:14:18.107 --> 00:14:19.907
We should have a drink sometime soon.
[laughs]

250
00:14:20.568 --> 00:14:22.945
Oh. I don't really drink. unfortunately.

251
00:14:23.654 --> 00:14:24.530
Huh.

252
00:14:24.613 --> 00:14:26.533
I'll be more than happy
to pour your drinks. sir.

253
00:14:27.491 --> 00:14:28.868
[both laughing]

254
00:14:31.078 --> 00:14:32.872
- Go on.
- Oh. okay.

255
00:14:39.128 --> 00:14:40.504
[inhales sharply]

256
00:14:58.606 --> 00:15:00.900
Use wasabi and soy sauce.

257
00:15:00.983 --> 00:15:03.277
[breathes deeply]

258
00:15:07.281 --> 00:15:08.407
Mm.

259
00:15:12.536 --> 00:15:14.163
[light rock music playing]

260
00:15:22.004 --> 00:15:23.005
Wild caught.

261
00:15:24.423 --> 00:15:28.886
You see. farmed halibut have a lot of fat
in their fins that can be too heavy.

262
00:15:28.969 --> 00:15:33.474
But wild ones like this
have all that fat evenly distributed.

263
00:15:33.557 --> 00:15:38.354
[inhales sharply]
It's such a clean and exquisite flavor.

264
00:15:39.605 --> 00:15:41.190
I can still taste it.

265
00:15:41.732 --> 00:15:43.150
And it's aged to perfection.

266
00:15:43.734 --> 00:15:44.777
Huh.

267
00:15:45.444 --> 00:15:47.821
